{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Department of Higher Education and Training |nativename = |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |seal = [[File:DHEAT logo.svg|250px]] |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = 2009 |preceding1 = [[Department of Education (South Africa)|Department of Education]] |jurisdiction = [[Government of South Africa]] |headquarters = [[Pretoria]] |coordinates = {{coord|25|45|00|S|28|11|03|E|type:landmark_region:ZA|display=inline}} |minister1_name = [[Naledi Pandor]] |minister1_pfo = [[Minister of Higher Education and Training (South Africa)|Minister of Higher Education and Training]] |minister2_name = [[Buti Manamela]] |minister2_pfo = Deputy Minister of Higher Education and Training |chief1_name = Gwebinkundla Qonde |chief1_position = Acting Director-General: Higher Education and Training |type = Department |keydocument1 = South African Higher Education Act, 1997 |website = [http://www.dhet.gov.za www.dhet.gov.za] |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = |logo=|employees=|budget=|chief2_name=|chief2_position=|chief3_name=|chief3_position=|chief4_name=|chief4_position=|chief5_name=|chief5_position=|chief6_name=|chief6_position=|chief7_name=|chief7_position=|chief8_name=|chief8_position=|chief9_name=|chief9_position=|parent_department=}}
The '''Department of Higher Education and Training''' is one of the [[ministry (government department)|departments]] of the [[Government of South Africa|South African government]]. It oversees [[universities]] and other [[post-secondary education]] in [[South Africa]]. It was created in 2009 after the election of [[President of South Africa|President]] [[Jacob Zuma]], when the former [[Department of Education (South Africa)|Department of Education]] was divided.
The political head of the department is the [[Minister of Higher Education and Training (South Africa)|Minister of Higher Education and Training]]; {{asof|2018|2|lc=on}} this is [[Naledi Pandor]]. The department is headquartered in Pretoria in what used to be known as Sol Plaatje House, named after the author and political activist [[Sol Plaatje]]. The name Sol Plaatje House is now used for the new [[Department of Basic Education]] building.
{{anchor|Journals}}The Department issues a [[Journal ranking by country|journal rank]] called "List of Approved South African Journals",<ref>http://www.researchoffice.uct.ac.za/usr/researchoffice/publication/DHET_Policy.pdf</ref> used as a criterion for South African scholars and scientists to receive recognition for their academic publishing productivity and for journal editors and publishers to receive monetary compensation from the government.<ref name="up.ac.za">{{cite web|url=http://www.library.up.ac.za/journals/journalsaccredited.htm|title=Department of Library Services|publisher=}}</ref><ref>http://rm.nmmu.ac.za/DHET-Accredited-Journal-Lists-for-publications-i</ref><ref name="up.ac.za"/><ref>http://www.researchoffice.uct.ac.za/usr/researchoffice/publication/PC%20Guide.pdf</ref>
