{{Infobox school | name = Georgetown International Academy | image = | alt = | caption = | motto = | location = 9-10 Delhi Street | city = [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]] | country = Guyana | coordinates = {{Coord|6.818258|-58.131122|region:GY_type:edu|display=inline,title}} | established = {{Start date|1971}} | opened = | closed = | type = | district = | grades = Nursery-12 | superintendent = | principal = | enrollment = 95 (as of 2011-12) | faculty = | campus_type = | campus_size = | team_name = | newspaper = | colors = | communities = | feeders = | website = {{URL|https://www.giagy.org/}} | footnotes = }} The '''Georgetown International Academy''' is a private, [[co-educational school|coeducational]] day school in [[Georgetown, Guyana]]. It offers an educational program compatible with the United States system for nursery through grade 12.
The school has been in operation since 1971. The school year comprises two semesters extending approximately from the end of August to the end of January and from the end of January to the middle of June.<ref name='USDOS-GIA'>{{cite web |url=https://www.state.gov/m/a/os/58563.htm |title=Guyana, Georgetown: Georgetown International Academy |accessdate=2012-09-08 |author=Under Secretary for Management » Bureau of Administration » Office of Overseas Schools » Schools Worldwide |work=US/DOS official web site |publisher=US Department of State |quote=The Georgetown International Academy is a private, coeducational day school which offers an educational program compatible with the United States system for nursery through grade 12. The School has been in operation since 1971. The school year comprises 2 semesters extending approximately from the end of August to the end of January and from the end of January to the middle of June. |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6AYmVGKDb?url=http://www.state.gov/m/a/os/58563.htm |archivedate=2012-09-09 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> <ref>This article is derived from a United States Department of State web site, a U.S. federal government work. U.S. federal government works are not eligible for copyright protection ([http://www.copyright.gov/title17/92chap1.html#105 17 USC 105]). {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6AYmVxksS?url=http://www.copyright.gov/title17/92chap1.html%23105 |date=September 9, 2012 }}</ref>
==Organization== The school is governed by a school board of seven members, elected by parents of the students for a two-year term. The school is incorporated in Guyana and operates within the laws of Guyana.<ref name='USDOS-GIA'/>
==Curriculum== The curriculum is largely that offered by United States elementary, middle and high schools, with additions intended to assist pupils in understanding Guyana and Caribbean geography and history. Textbooks are current and are from major U.S. educational publishers. The school is fully accredited by [[AdvancED]] ([[Southern Association of Colleges and Schools]] (SACS)).<ref name='USDOS-GIA'/>
==Faculty== In the 2011–2012 school year, there were fourteen full-time and four part-time teachers, and three teaching assistants.<ref name='USDOS-GIA'/>
==Enrollment== At the beginning of the 2011–2012 school year, enrollment was 95. * Nursery/Kindergarten: 15 * Grades 1–6: 33 * Grades 7–12: 46<ref name='USDOS-GIA'/>
==Facilities== The school is located at 9-10 Delhi Street, Prashad Nagar, Georgetown,<ref name='GIA-Contact'>{{cite web |url=http://www.georgetowninternationalacademy.org/contactus.html |title=Contact Us |accessdate=2012-09-08 |author=GIA |work=GIA official web site |publisher=Georgetown International Academy |quote=Address: 9-10 Delhi Street Prashad Nagar Georgetown, Guyana. |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6AYmW50s8?url=http://www.georgetowninternationalacademy.org/contactus.html |archivedate=2012-09-09 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> and housed in three buildings, one of which is undergoing extensive renovation. The small campus includes classrooms a science lab, a computer lab, a school library, art and music rooms, physical education and an assembly/lunch area. There are also two play areas including a new early-childhood play center.<ref name='USDOS-GIA'/>
